HEADWORD: Libellee
<hw>Li`bel*lee"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The party against whom a libel has been filed; --
corresponding to <altname>defendant</altname> in a common law
action.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The defendant in an action of
libel.</def>⟦br⟧
